Vice President Mike Pence visited Georgia during his trip to Eastern Europe. He met with Prime Minister Giorgi Kvirikashvili to discuss the United States' condemnation of Russia's occupation of Georgia's soil. Pence and his wife also toured the Sioni Cathedral of the Dormition with religious leaders. Pence addressed American and Georgian troops at Exercise Noble Partner, highlighting their shared commitment to security and stability. He then departed for Montenegro, the last stop of his Eastern Europe visit.